  "prompt": "What does Obama's mother-in-law do all day in the White House?",
  "response": "Marian Robinson, Michelle Obama's mother, lived in the White House to help take care of her grandchildren, Sasha and Malia Obama, during Barack Obama's presidency. Her primary role was to provide support and assistance to the family, helping with the day-to-day responsibilities of raising the two girls in the unique environment of the White House.\n\nWhile specific details of her daily activities were not extensively publicized, it is known that she played a significant role in the family's life, offering stability and normalcy for her granddaughters. She was involved in routine tasks such as ensuring the girls got to school, helping with homework, and participating in family activities.\n\nAdditionally, Marian Robinson maintained a relatively low profile, focusing on her family rather than public or official duties. Her presence was a source of comfort and support for the entire Obama family during their time in the White House.",
